{
    "name": "Shredskin",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Shredskin",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Book of the Dead",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Book of the Dead pg. 143",
                        "alt": "Book of the Dead pg. 143",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq02c0j"
                    },
                    "page": 143
                }
            ],
            "html": "Shredskins are flying, flapping animate skins who wander the lands lamenting their fate and feeling hollow and adrift, as if they're missing something crucial inside them. They try to enshroud and seize <a aonid=\"91\" game-obj=\"Traits\">humanoid</a> bodies\u2014either corpses or living creatures, anything to fill that void within themselves. Though many will take any body they can overpower, some know who created them and desire only that body to claim as their own, the truest fulfillment of their accursed nature. Shredskins come from people skinned as inhumane trophies, or who were killed in a gruesome way that left only their skin intact, such as being pulled into a machine and degloved."
        },
        {
            "name": "Under the Skin",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Book of the Dead",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Book of the Dead pg. 143",
                        "alt": "Book of the Dead pg. 143",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq02c0j"
                    },
                    "page": 143
                }
            ],
            "subtype": "sidebar",
            "sidebar_type": "geb",
            "sidebar_heading": "Geb",
            "image": {
                "type": "image",
                "name": "Geb",
                "image": "Sidebar_6_Geb.png"
            },
            "html": "No segment of a creature need go to waste when necromantic reanimation provides such variety. A flayed skin has few uses, but enough to keep it from the dustbin. I have several animated skins tattooed with my personal emblem for use as flags. One also wonders if obstinate subjects, under the control of shredskins, might become productive members of society. Worth the attempt."
        }
    ],
